      • normalise

        public ListPattern normalise(ListPattern pattern)
        Description copied from class: DomainSpecifics
        Used to prepare ListPatterns for input to long-term memory by a Chrest model. Implementing this enables Modality.VISUAL ListPatterns to be stripped of ItemSquarePatterns that denote empty Squares in a Scene, for example.
        Specified by:
        normalise in class DomainSpecifics
        Parameters:
        pattern -
        Returns:
        A ListPattern stripped of ItemSquarePatterns that:
        1. Represents the agent equipped with the associated Chrest model.
        2. Represent blind/empty Squares.
        3. Are duplicated in the ListPattern passed.

      • getNonInitialFixationInSet

        public Fixation getNonInitialFixationInSet(int time)
        Description copied from class: DomainSpecifics
        Used by Chrest.scheduleOrMakeNextFixation(jchrest.domainSpecifics.Scene, boolean, boolean, int).
        Specified by:
        getNonInitialFixationInSet in class DomainSpecifics
        Parameters:
        time -
        Returns:
        A HypothesisDiscriminationFixation should always be returned unless:
        1. There is such a Fixation already being deliberated on by the associated Chrest model but hasn't been performed yet.
        2. The most recent Fixation attempted was a HypothesisDiscriminationFixation but it wasn't performed successfully.
        In the first case, the outcome of attempting to make the HypothesisDiscriminationFixation is unknown so instead of generating another which may fail again (essentially wasting a Fixation since only a finite number can be attempted (see DomainSpecifics.getMaximumFixationsInSet()), generate another type of Fixation.

        In the second case, the outcome of attempting to make a HypothesisDiscriminationFixation is known and the attempt was unsuccessful so other Fixations need to be attempted to try and replace the hypothesis present in the Modality.VISUAL Stm of the Chrest model associated with this GenericDomain since its information is not useful in the current Scene being fixated on.

      • shouldLearnFromNewFixations

        public boolean shouldLearnFromNewFixations(int time)
        Description copied from class: DomainSpecifics
        Used by Chrest.scheduleOrMakeNextFixation(jchrest.domainSpecifics.Scene, boolean, boolean, int) to determine if any Fixations successfully performed by the Perceiver associated with the Chrest model invoking Chrest.scheduleOrMakeNextFixation(jchrest.domainSpecifics.Scene, boolean, boolean, int) that have not been learned yet, should be. NOTE: Chrest.scheduleOrMakeNextFixation(jchrest.domainSpecifics.Scene, boolean, boolean, int) already checks for a SceneObject or Square being focused on again since the last time Chrest.scheduleOrMakeNextFixation(jchrest.domainSpecifics.Scene, boolean, boolean, int) was invoked.
        Specified by:
        shouldLearnFromNewFixations in class DomainSpecifics
        Parameters:
        time -
        Returns:
        Boolean.FALSE since there are no extra conditions to consider when a Chrest model using this GenericDomain determines whether the Fixations it has performed should be learned from.
